Cass Sunstein, who has served for the last three and a half years, has made significant accomplishments during his time in office. He has implemented protections for American families, reduced paperwork burdens for citizens and businesses, and promoted economic growth while prioritizing health, safety, and the environment. Sunstein has also led efforts to review and eliminate costly or unnecessary regulations, resulting in potential savings of billions of dollars. The President expresses gratitude for his friendship and exceptional service.